  "texts": [
    "We prove the B-case.",
    "Recall first that π φa = φ(κ a) (Definition and notation 3.1.5.",
    "If π φa ⊂ κ b then in view of Proposition 3.2.6 there exists a function f ∶ A → B such that (id J, f) is a B-map from φa to b.",
    "Now in view of Proposition 4.1.2 this implies that (φ, f) is a B-map from a to b.",
    "The proof of the B-case is similar, with reference to Proposition 3.2.12 instead of Proposition 3.2.6."
  ],
